HEADWORD: manticore
<hw>manticore</hw></mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <def>A mythical monster having the head of man (with
horns) and the body of a lion and the tail of a scorpion.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> manticore, mantichora, mantiger.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

